page.title: 01General Review NE Woking.
page.content: The area is traversed from south-west to north-east by the Portsmouth-London railway, the Basingstoke canal and the A320 road from Woking to Chertsey.It consists of the north of Woking town, the Sheerwater industrial estate and parts of the villages of Woodham and Pyrford. The north is mainly heathland common and wood, with small farms and golf courses. The housing is varied with expensive private property in the south and council houses and mixed property around the edge of Woking town. There is a NHS hospital as well as a private hospital. Several large properties have been converted into homes for the elderly and small private schools. The first mosque in England, dating from 1889, is located near the railway in the south and forms the focus for a large Asian community in the area.
